  <heading>BF1CVT, BF2CVT</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>8-bit floating-point convert to BFloat16</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction converts each even-numbered 8-bit floating-point element of the source vector
to BFloat16 while downscaling the value, and places the results
in the overlapping 16-bit elements of the destination vector.
BF1CVT scales the values by 2<sup>-UInt(FPMR.LSCALE[5:0])</sup>.
BF2CVT scales the values by 2<sup>-UInt(FPMR.LSCALE2[5:0])</sup>.</para>
      <para>The 8-bit floating-point encoding format for BF1CVT is selected by <asm-code>FPMR.F8S1</asm-code>.
The 8-bit floating-point encoding format for BF2CVT is selected by <asm-code>FPMR.F8S2</asm-code>.</para>
      <para>This instruction is unpredicated.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>False</predicated>
  </desc>
